There was at least one other.

12
00:00:31,340 --> 00:00:33,580
Her name was Johanna.

13
00:00:33,590 --> 00:00:35,180
Oh,my God.

14
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:36,850
Marion Wheeler?

15
00:00:36,860 --> 00:00:38,720
Are you the owner of this store?

16
00:00:38,730 --> 00:00:40,180
Maybe.

17
00:00:40,190 --> 00:00:41,550
Johanna?

18
00:00:41,560 --> 00:00:45,160
Her disappearance in 1998?

19
00:00:45,220 --> 00:00:47,640
My daughter isn't missing.
She's never been missing.

20
00:00:47,650 --> 00:00:49,150
It means you're wrong.

21
00:00:49,160 --> 00:00:50,560
It means I'm actually...

22
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:53,310
I'm actually angry that that
woman's daughter isn't dead

23
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:55,970
because she could have been there
for daughter in her final moments,

24
00:00:56,010 --> 00:00:58,750
if in fact,if she was
ever even in that basement.

25
00:00:58,780 --> 00:00:59,710
What does that mean?

26
00:00:59,740 --> 00:01:01,060
It means you're fired.

27
00:01:01,070 --> 00:01:03,670
Slow down. Are you
telling me you think you...

28
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,450
you actually invented something?

29
00:01:05,460 --> 00:01:06,970
Here's the thingit isn't just a toy.

30
00:01:06,980 --> 00:01:09,690
I actually think that it might
have real world applications.

31
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:12,320
I figure all that's going
to cost about $30,000.

32
00:01:12,330 --> 00:01:14,900
Joe,come on.

33
00:01:14,910 --> 00:01:18,250
$30,000? We don't even have $3,000.

34
00:01:18,260 --> 00:01:19,580
The girl's college money.

35
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:22,640
There's almost $32,000
just sitting there.

36
00:01:22,650 --> 00:01:24,340
You know I can't do this.

37
00:01:24,350 --> 00:01:26,810
God,isn't life funny?

38
00:01:26,830 --> 00:01:30,090
I mean,this whole marriage has
always been about me believing in you.

39
00:01:30,110 --> 00:01:33,660
Now the one time,the one time,the
shoe ends up on the other foot...

40
00:01:33,670 --> 00:01:35,240
This is not the same thing.

41
00:01:35,290 --> 00:01:37,690
It's exactly the same thing,exactly.

42
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,220
Where are you going?

43
00:01:39,230 --> 00:01:40,000
What does it matter?

44
00:01:40,010 --> 00:01:40,910
Joe...

45
00:01:40,950 --> 00:01:43,570
Stop it,please!

46
00:01:44,530 --> 00:01:47,980
Oh,God... oh,God.Oh,God.

