60
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:38,530
Next time that thing rings,answer it.

61
00:03:38,540 --> 00:03:40,450
Might be an emergency.

62
00:03:40,460 --> 00:03:43,440
Maybe she needs your help.

63
00:03:43,450 --> 00:03:46,050
Reporting live from just
outside Casa Valley Hospital

64
00:03:46,060 --> 00:03:51,270
where the two young women managed to escape
from their captor early this morning...

65
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,990
Actually,it looks like
she's doing just fine.

66
00:03:54,010 --> 00:03:57,170
Looks like she's right
where she wants to be.

67
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:04,190
Ms. Keener.

68
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:06,670
One of your colleagues from
Ameritips is asking for you.

69
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:09,020
She's in the waiting area.

70
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:13,950
I'm sorry.

71
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,260
I know I'm not supposed to be here.

72
00:04:15,270 --> 00:04:16,460
I'm supposed to be a secret.

73
00:04:16,470 --> 00:04:18,260
I have to talk to you about something.

74
00:04:18,270 --> 00:04:22,670
Everything I've been seeing in my dreams
the last few nights,everything about Suzie--

75
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:23,520
it happened.

76
00:04:23,550 --> 00:04:25,080
It did not happen.

77
00:04:25,110 --> 00:04:27,960
Not to my daughter,not nine years ago.

78
00:04:27,990 --> 00:04:29,460
We know that now.

79
00:04:29,490 --> 00:04:31,670
What you saw was happening
to Melanie Linder.

80
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,370
You got the faces confused.

81
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:36,280
- You put Suzie's face where Melanie's was,and...
- No.

82
00:04:36,290 --> 00:04:38,030
I think I got the faces right:

83
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:41,320
Suzie's,Johanna
Wheeler's,the kidnapper's.

84
00:04:41,350 --> 00:04:42,930
That makes no sense.

85
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:44,340
Johanna Wheeler was just freed.

86
00:04:44,350 --> 00:04:48,280
Obviously,she wasn't locked up in a
basement with my daughter nine years ago.

87
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,740
I think she was.

88
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:53,740
What are you saying?

89
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:55,360
She was in on it.

90
00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:57,640
She and her boyfriend.

91
00:04:57,650 --> 00:05:02,560
He's not the man who took Suzie,but I believe
he and Johanna had the same arrangement.

92
00:05:02,570 --> 00:05:04,400
What do you mean?

93
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:08,670
They would
target a girl--

94
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,830
someone they both wanted.

95
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:14,330
And the boyfriend would kidnap her and
throw her in the basement with Johanna

96
00:05:14,350 --> 00:05:17,300
who would pretend to be a fellow victim.

97
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:19,160
Why would she do that?

98
00:05:19,170 --> 00:05:22,190
Because she's a sociopath.

99
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:24,620
Because she thinks it's fun.

100
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:28,130
Because it's all a big game to her.

101
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:30,530
She likes
befriending them--

102
00:05:30,550 --> 00:05:36,210
getting them to open up,seducing them,keeping
them close to her,and then watching...

103
00:05:37,250 --> 00:05:40,140
their surprise when she betrays them.

104
00:05:40,170 --> 00:05:43,700
Laughing while they're suffering.

105
00:05:44,130 --> 00:05:47,630
Well,I saw Johanna when
they brought her in.

106
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:50,020
She didn't look like she
was playing a game to me.

107
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,860
She's acting.

108
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:54,700
For you,for the police,for the media.

109
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,140
She has to.

110
00:05:56,150 --> 00:06:00,740
The last thing she imagined was that Melanie
Linder would get that gun away from her boyfriend

111
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:04,530
and kill him with it,before
they could kill her.

112
00:06:05,820 --> 00:06:08,010
Well,that's a very
interesting theory,Allison.

113
00:06:08,020 --> 00:06:13,640
The only problem is,Melanie Linder wasn't the
one who wrestled the gun away from the kidnapper.

114
00:06:13,650 --> 00:06:16,990
Melanie Linder wasn't
the one who shot him.

115
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,670
It was Johanna Wheeler.

116
00:06:23,090 --> 00:06:25,240
I'm home.

117
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:33,840
You smell like beer.

118
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,650
I don't know what to tell you.

119
00:06:40,660 --> 00:06:42,930
It's not our money to use.

120
00:06:42,940 --> 00:06:45,850
It's the girls' money.

121
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:48,430
I'm sorry.

122
00:06:52,350 --> 00:06:55,950
Do you want to pick up the
girls or you want me to do it?

123
00:06:57,470 --> 00:07:00,810
You're right. You probably
shouldn't be driving.

124
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:11,270
Please...

125
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:13,580
please don't.

126
00:07:13,590 --> 00:07:16,110
Please.

127
00:07:22,010 --> 00:07:23,860
Don't.

128
00:07:25,690 --> 00:07:29,420
If you have to take one of us...

129
00:07:30,490 --> 00:07:32,900
take me.

130
00:07:37,060 --> 00:07:39,540
If you take her,she'll just keep crying.

131
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:42,570
Me...

132
00:07:42,580 --> 00:07:46,070
I can make you believe I like it.

133
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:24,570
Not yet.

134
00:08:25,530 --> 00:08:28,670
I have to check my messages.

135
00:08:31,670 --> 00:08:33,230
Hey,sweetie,it's Mom.

136
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:39,110
Listen,Johanna,I'm sorry to bother you with
this,but the strangest thing just happened.

137
00:08:39,610 --> 00:08:42,950
These two women came to
visit me here at the store.

138
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,900
One of them was a private investigator

139
00:08:44,910 --> 00:08:49,710
and they both seemed to be under
the impression that something...

140
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:54,590
well,that something terrible
happened to you nine years ago.

141
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,510
I mean,obviously they have
the wrong Johanna Wheeler,

142
00:08:56,530 --> 00:09:00,880
but I don't know,I just thought
you should know just in case.

143
00:09:02,020 --> 00:09:04,380
Next message...

144
00:09:04,390 --> 00:09:06,140
Hello,Ms. Wheeler.

145
00:09:06,150 --> 00:09:09,800
My name is Cynthia Keener and I'm
an investigator with Ameritips.

146
00:09:09,820 --> 00:09:12,420
I'm calling because it recently
came to my attention that

147
00:09:12,430 --> 00:09:18,710
you may have some information regarding a
missing persons case involving a Suzanne Keener.

148
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:22,260
If you'd call me at your earliest
convenience I'd appreciate it.

149
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:24,940
I can be reached at...

150
00:09:34,090 --> 00:09:37,120
**********

151
00:09:50,330 --> 00:09:51,890
Daddy?

152
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:54,550
Daddy,you up?

153
00:09:54,930 --> 00:09:58,540
Bridge... You all right?

154
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:01,140
Everything all right?

155
00:10:01,150 --> 00:10:03,840
Why are you sleeping in here?

156
00:10:03,850 --> 00:10:07,260
I don't know. It's fun.

157
00:10:08,970 --> 00:10:11,860
Sweetie,what is it?

158
00:10:11,870 --> 00:10:14,540
I think you need to
go to the bank,Daddy.

159
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,370
What are you talking about?

160
00:10:16,410 --> 00:10:17,920
Well,you need money,right?

161
00:10:17,930 --> 00:10:20,430
I heard you and Mommy talking about it.

162
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:23,950
Yeah,but,Bridge,no one at the bank
is just going to give us money.

163
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:25,200
But they are.

164
00:10:25,210 --> 00:10:26,960
I had a dream about it.

165
00:10:26,970 --> 00:10:31,480
There's this white-haired man working
there,and he wants to give you a bunch of money.

166
00:10:31,490 --> 00:10:34,300
A white-haired man?

167
00:10:35,180 --> 00:10:37,490
Bridge,this
white-haired man--

168
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:40,480
he wouldn't be Santa by any chance?

169
00:10:40,490 --> 00:10:41,890
Dad,come on.

170
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:45,250
I'm nine. Trust me.

171
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:55,570
Allison,what are you doing here?

172
00:10:55,580 --> 00:10:57,820
Do you have any idea what time it is?

173
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:01,790
Did you leave a message for Johanna Wheeler
after we met her mother the other day?

174
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,360
Well,yes,I did.

175
00:11:03,370 --> 00:11:06,520
I wanted to make absolutely
sure she didn't know my daughter.

176
00:11:06,530 --> 00:11:07,430
Why?

177
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:12,540
Her mother left her a
message too,at we were asking

178
00:11:12,550 --> 00:11:15,460
Yesterday you asked me if Johanna
and David Draper were partners,

179
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:18,710
why would she kill him before
they finished their little game.

180
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:21,940
Well,now I think I know the answer.

181
00:11:21,950 --> 00:11:24,180
It was us,Cynthia.

182
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:26,790
We're the reason that she killed him.

183
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:29,400
We spooked her.

184
00:11:31,660 --> 00:11:37,780
This is Peter Connolly,the man that
I saw torturing Suzie in my dreams.

185
00:11:37,790 --> 00:11:42,990
The man I believe was working
with Johanna Wheeler in 1998.

186
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,670
You think that I'm wrong?

187
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,810
Let's talk to Johanna Wheeler.

188
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:51,020
Let's talk to Peter Connolly.

189
00:12:03,070 --> 00:12:04,390
Can I help you,sir?

190
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:06,730
Uh,I don't know,maybe.

191
00:12:07,090 --> 00:12:11,070
Um,a friend of mine recommended that I come
and speak to a colleague of yours about a loan,

192
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:13,040
but I'm having a hard
time remembering his name.

193
00:12:13,060 --> 00:12:15,800
All I know for sure is
that he has white hair.

194
00:12:15,810 --> 00:12:18,450
Oh,you mean Walter.

195
00:12:20,890 --> 00:12:24,450
Walter,yes. Good ol' Walter.

196
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:28,860
Miss Wheeler?

197
00:12:29,630 --> 00:12:30,940
Do you have a moment?

198
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:33,110
If you're reporters,the press
conference is downstairs.

199
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:35,810
I'm not giving any interviews.

200
00:12:35,820 --> 00:12:39,250
Actually,I'm an
investigator with Ameritips.

201
00:12:39,260 --> 00:12:42,070
My name is Cynthia Keener.

202
00:12:44,830 --> 00:12:47,940
You,uh,left a message on my cell,right?

203
00:12:47,950 --> 00:12:50,670
Something about a missing persons case?

204
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:52,140
That's right.

205
00:12:52,150 --> 00:12:55,200
I listened to it this morning when the
police returned my personal effects,

206
00:12:55,210 --> 00:12:59,130
but I didn't understand it.

207
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:02,450
No one I know has ever gone missing;

208
00:13:02,460 --> 00:13:07,360
no family,no friends,no
one except myself,really.

209
00:13:08,390 --> 00:13:10,350
I don't see how I could be of any help.

210
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:13,350
Well,we were wondering if maybe you'd
be willing to look at a few photographs,

211
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:16,290
tell us if you recognize
any of the people in there.

212
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:19,240
Of course,if you think it would help.

213
00:13:22,860 --> 00:13:25,360
I'm sorry. I don't know her.

214
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:34,380
How about this man?

215
00:13:38,060 --> 00:13:41,850
Maybe you'd like to look
again just to make sure.

216
00:13:48,030 --> 00:13:51,030
I've never seen this
man before in my life.

217
00:13:52,750 --> 00:13:57,620
Well,obviously,the anonymous
tip my office received was bogus.

218
00:13:57,630 --> 00:14:00,430
It happens sometimes.

219
00:14:01,370 --> 00:14:05,290
I'm sorry. I'm confused.

220
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:12,120
Are you saying that someone told you I had
information about a missing persons case?

221
00:14:12,130 --> 00:14:17,050
Well,earlier this week,my
office received a tip that

222
00:14:17,060 --> 00:14:23,160
this man Peter Connolly
abducted two young women in 1998.

223
00:14:23,170 --> 00:14:29,210
He kept them in a basement,raped them
repeatedly,tortured them,then discarded them.

224
00:14:29,710 --> 00:14:32,610
According to the
person who contacted me,

225
00:14:32,620 --> 00:14:36,640
one of these young women
was my daughter Suzie.

226
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:39,520
The other one was you.

227
00:14:41,430 --> 00:14:45,740
This some sort of joke?

228
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:50,850
I was kidnapped this week.

229
00:14:50,860 --> 00:14:53,990
I was raped this week.

230
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,870
If the same thing had
happened to me nine years ago,

231
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:59,040
don't you think I would have
mentioned it to the police?

232
00:14:59,050 --> 00:15:04,430
If this is a joke,it's being
had at both of our expenses.

233
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:08,410
Obviously,I love my daughter
very much,Miss Wheeler,

234
00:15:08,420 --> 00:15:11,520
and I would do anything to
find out what happened to her,

235
00:15:11,530 --> 00:15:17,000
even risk upsetting you at what
is clearly a very difficult time.

236
00:15:17,010 --> 00:15:19,280
Please forgive me.

237
00:15:21,230 --> 00:15:27,090
Have you talked to him yet,this,uh,this
Connolly person,the one in the photograph?

238
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:30,480
No,not yet. He's next on our list.Why?

239
00:15:30,490 --> 00:15:33,160
According to the
person who contacted me,

240
00:15:33,170 --> 00:15:39,610
this man Connolly had a lot in common with
the man who kidnapped you and Melanie Linder.

241
00:15:40,510 --> 00:15:43,320
You know,Ms. Dubois and
I keep asking ourselves,

242
00:15:43,330 --> 00:15:45,950
"Was there any connection
between these two men?

243
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:46,910
"Did they know each other?

244
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:50,320
"Was there communication
between them at some point?

245
00:15:50,330 --> 00:15:53,220
"Did they frequent the same nightclubs?

246
00:15:53,230 --> 00:15:56,260
Perhaps they trolled
the same chatrooms."

247
00:15:56,270 --> 00:15:58,220
Or who knows?

248
00:15:58,460 --> 00:16:01,420
Maybe they dated the same woman.

249
00:16:03,860 --> 00:16:07,200
I suppose anything is possible.

250
00:16:10,110 --> 00:16:13,360
Very sorry I couldn't be
of more help,Ms. Keener.

251
00:16:13,380 --> 00:16:17,750
Maybe you'll have more luck
with this Connolly fellow.

252
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:19,970
